Laureline is indeed supposed to be quite young but Valerian should be at least in his mid-twenties. Also, the tone looks too flippant and the emphasis seems to be on action. The graphic novels were dreamy and rather slow, letting one bask in the wonders of the worlds explored. Of course, I'll see it, and I understand the commercial imperatives of catering to a young audience.
